~Bah <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uwisbus2k1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wisbus2k1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(6/28/01 5:47:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=708.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Need some help with quest armor - Agnostic</span><hr size=1> Yeah, do hate raids. Its good old-world armor, and apothic is the staple robe for magicians. If you can goto Velious, you should consider doing Kael / PoG raids. <br>
<br>
Why PoG, doesn't that mess up my faction? <br>
<br>
Yes, but what do you need that faction for? Avoid the cleric / paladin guild in felwithie, and most of the guilds in kelethin. You can still bank there, guards wont mind.<br>
<br>
On Tunare, the server i play on, there are very few mages who do PoG, so building seniority isn't too much of a worry. <br>
<br>
<br>
If you are in a larger, well organized guild then Skyshrine armor / kael armor will be your best bet (pog robe / thur robe look the best on gnomes &gt;)   <br>
<br>
Best of luck<br>
<br>
Wisbus <br>
55 conjurer<br>
